Author: p3d_pilot
Content: PK-GPA, age as of right now, 28.3 years old

Author: p3d_pilot
Content: delivered fresh from Airbus in December 1996, she served GA faithfully, until she was stored in 27 Jul 2021. She was powered by the weakest derivative of the Trent 700, Trent 768-60, with just 68,500 lbf of thrust in each engine, Unlike her Younger sister, GPZ which is powered by the 772B-60, able to crank out 71,100 lbf of thrust from each engine

Author: p3d_pilot
Content: She's so old, she saw service with Hong Kong Kai Tak

Author: p3d_pilot
Content: Until 2009, she was configured with 24 business class, and 251 economy, before being reconfigured with 24 business and 215 economy. She got the Liverpool Football Club sticker between July 2013 and February 2014, where she was returned to the brand refresh look, and stayed so until March 2021. Between August 2015 and March 2021, she was configured with 360 economy, likely focusing on high density routes like Jakarta-Bali or Jakarta Medan. From march 2021 onwards, she was stripped of her seats and configured as preighter, being applied with the Cargo titles of Garuda Indonesia, and since Jul 27th 2021, she was stored at CGK GMF Aeroasia.
